title: Sydney Man Sentenced To 16 Years In Prison Over Deadly Road Rage Attack | 10 News
description: A man has been sentenced to 16 years in prison for a road rage attack that killed a man in Western Sydney. Bradley Wilkinson cut off Rhyce Harding's car while Wilkinson was running late for work. When they argued, he then ran over the younger man and did not stop to help. title: Prince William Opens Up On How His Children Dealt With Kate Cancer Diagnosis | 10 News
description: Prince William has told of the methods he has used to help his children understand his wife, Catherine, Princess of Wales' 2024 cancer diagnosis, as well as his father, King Charles III's battle with cancer.  William said he and Kate chose to communicate the issues with their children, to the point where he felt as if sometimes they were "oversharing".  He also spoke of the world he would like to leave for his son George, when he eventually ascends to the throne as King, saying he would like to improve the environmental situation around the world, as it has a direct link to social issues.
